). Specimens were examined with a Leica M165C stereomicroscope. Photographs of preserved specimens were taken with a Leica DFC 290 digital camera mounted on a M165C stereomicroscope, or a Zeiss AxioCam 105 Color adapted on a Zeiss Primo Star microscope. Extended focal range images composed with Helicon Focus 8.0.2 Pro software (http://www.heliconsoft.com/heliconsoftproducts/helicon-focus/). Drawings were made based on the photographs of the genitalia, checking details on an Olympus SZ40 stereomicroscope. All figures were prepared in Adobe Lightroom Classic 11.5® and assembled in CorelDraw® 2019. Measurements are expressed in millimeters and were taken using a using a Nikon SMZ 445 stereomicroscope equipped with ocular micrometer. The distribution map was produced using ArcGIS 10.3 (
). Abbreviations: BL = basal ledge; BU = bulb; CY = cymbium; E = embolus; LE = laminar expansion; MR = median receptacles; PP = pore plates.

